post_text:
From CHS Athletics Director Todd Hague:

It's a big week at Cheney High School as we get into the postseason!

The Cross County team qualified three runners, Ethan Albers, Abbye Hudson, and Mollie Reno. They will run Saturday morning in Lawrence at Rim Rock Farm.

Volleyball won a tough Sub State tournament at Haven and advance to State as the #4 seed. State is at the Sports Arena in Hutch and we play at 8:30 Friday morning.

Football concluded the regular season with a hard fought game at Andale last week. Although it was a loss, our team has had a great year as we finished 6-2 and District Runner Up. We will host a first round playoff game on Friday night vs Rock Creek.

State Recap from the Girls Golf Team.
https://cheneyathletics.com/recap/girls-varsity-golf-finishes-10th-place-at-state-salina-municipal-course/

Southern Plains Marching Festival. Here is the link to the live feed: https://www.nfhsnetwork.com/events/andover-high-school-andover-ks/gamc208baacb4

Hope to see everyone at the events this week. We have much to be proud of and much more to play for!

post_text:
CHS Activities Update - Todd Hague/AD

Congrats to the Volleyball Team on their outstanding season and finish as State Runner Up last weekend!

The Football team won their playoff game and advance to the Regional round on Saturday. We will host Marion at 2:00, gates open at 12:30. No home passes are allowed, as it's a KSHSAA event. $6 Adult and $5 Student admission. This is only the third time in school history that we've made the Regional round so let's pack the stands on Saturday and get loud! The game will be broadcast on KXKU 106.1 starting at 1:45 PM.

Cardinal Club will be hosting a Chili Tailgate on Saturday at 12:00. $5 gets you chili, dessert and a drink. Come enjoy the pregame with a meal!

The Fall Sports Social for CHS is being postponed to Thursday, November 16th at 7:00. Keep it rolling football team!

The Fall Play is scheduled for performances on Friday the 10th and Saturday the 11th for the, "The Snow White Variety Show". Come check it out and enjoy the show!

post_text:
From: Todd Hague, AD

The Cheney High School Boys Basketball team is headed to State!

We'd like to have a community send off for all that want to be involved. On Thursday the boys will load the Cardinal Bus at 12:45 and go on Lake Road to the south end of town. They'll head north on Main Street and we want to send them off right!

Poke your head out of the businesses and line the streets with signs and well wishes if you can!

Elementary, Middle and High School students that are able will be released to line Main Street and do the same.

Thanks for all of your support and Go Cardinals!

post_text:
Greetings from CHS,
Just a reminder the deadline for the CHS Alumni Banquet is September 1st.

On Friday, September 19th, the Cardinal football team will play host to Wichita Independent. Game time is 7:00 PM with the Homecoming ceremonies taking place at 6:30 PM.

Also we are excited to announce that author Steve Farney will be in attendance at the Cardinal Party taking place at the Farm Bureau building at the Fairgrounds immediately after the banquet. Steve has authored various books about Kansas High School Basketball. His book entitled "Streakin'" is about the Kansas teams who have won 50 or more consecutive games. The CHS Girls Basketball teams from 2008-2011 are included and some players will be available at the Cardinal Party. Mr. Farney has graciously agreed to donate $2 dollars from every book sold that night to the Alumni Association.

Hope to see you in September!!
